JOURNAL ARTICLE
Unions and Workers’ Welfare in Chinese Firms
https://www.jstor.org/stable/10.1086/669819

pension coverage 养老金的覆盖面
individual and collective contracts（集体合同）

the SUR model for three subsamples domestic private enterprises(DPEs), manufacturing firms, and firms in Guangdong Province.
1. The DPEs are less likely to establish unions, and their labor protection is weaker than that of either SOEs or foeign-invested enterprises(FIEs).
2. Manufacturing is more competitive in the product market than other sectors, and competition may force firms to cut workers' benefits.
3. Guangdong accounts for one-third of China's exports, and it has the largest presence of migrant workers. As a result, informalization may be more severe there than in other parts of the country.



